css:
/* 
Dank Drudge
© 2012 Chris Blackburn

I began with M.andrew's DARK DRUDGE REPORT and modified it slightly.  

Here is the original copyright:

DARK DRUDGE REPORT
© 2012 M.andrew

The Drudge is a great site in need of a dark-over. In an effort to
preserve the original logo, I settle for a shade of gray instead
of the full white-on-black experience - but it still looks bad.

Changelog:
1.2 - Themed poll and input areas
1.1 - Added #EEE color clause to body style to match #222 background
1.0 - Release
*/

@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);
@-moz-document domain('drudgereport.com') {


body{
background: #222 !important;
color: #EEE !important;
}

a{
text-decoration: none !important;
}
a:link{
color: #0e0 !important;
}
a:hover{
text-decoration: underline !important;
}
a:visited{
color: #660 !important;
}
a:active{
color: #0EE !important;
}


img{
border: 1px solid #fff !important;
}

a img{
border: 3px solid black !important;
background: white !important;
box-shadow: 0 0 25px #555555;
}

.pds-box {
background: #000 !important;
}
.pds-question-top {
color: #FFF !important;
}
.pds-answer-span {
color: #FFF !important;
}
.pds-vote-button {
background: #333 !important;
}

input,textarea {
background: #000 !important;
color: #FFF !important;
-moz-appearance: none !important;
}

hr {
height: 12px;
border: 0;
box-shadow: inset 0 12px 12px -12px rgba(1,150,1,0.5);
}


}
